title: Shenzhen Open semi-finals are a wash-out
text:
Shenzhen Open semi-finals are a wash-out 03 Oct 2015 13:46:58 
comments 
The semi-finals of the Shenzhen Open have been moved to Sunday after persistent rain saw both matches washed out on Saturday. 
Top seed Tomas Berdych had been scheduled to face third seed Tommy Robredo in the first semi-final on Saturday with the later clash seeing second seed Marin Cilic take on Guillermo Garcia-Lopez, the fourth seed. 
Both matches will now be played simultaneously on centre court and court 1 at 1300 local time on Sunday before the winners face each other in the final, which will start at 1730 at the earliest. Related Sport News
